verses.text_plain: Adam, Sheth, Enosh,
verses.verse_html: 1Adam, Sheth, Enosh,

verses.text_plain: Kenan, Mahalaleel, Jered,
verses.verse_html: 2Kenan, Mahalaleel, Jered,

verses.text_plain: Henoch, Methuselah, Lamech,
verses.verse_html: 3Henoch, Methuselah, Lamech,

verses.text_plain: Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.
verses.verse_html: 4Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth.

verses.text_plain: The sons of Japheth; Gomer, and Magog, and Madai, and Javan, and Tubal, and Meshech, and Tiras.
verses.verse_html: 5The sons of Japheth; Gomer, and Magog, and Madai, and Javan, and Tubal, and Meshech, and Tiras.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Gomer; Ashchenaz, and Riphath, and Togarmah.
verses.verse_html:
6And the sons of Gomer; Ashchenaz, and Riphath, and Togarmah. ▼
▼ Riphath: or, Diphath as it is in some copies

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Riphath: or, Diphath as it is in some copies
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Riphath: or, Diphath as it is in some copies

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Javan; Elishah, and Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim.
verses.verse_html:
7And the sons of Javan; Elishah, and Tarshish, Kittim, and Dodanim. ▼
▼ Dodanim: or, Rodanim, according to some copies

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Dodanim: or, Rodanim, according to some copies
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Dodanim: or, Rodanim, according to some copies

verses.text_plain: The sons of Ham; Cush, and Mizraim, Put, and Canaan.
verses.verse_html: 8The sons of Ham; Cush, and Mizraim, Put, and Canaan.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Cush; Seba, and Havilah, and Sabta, and Raamah, and Sabtecha. And the sons of Raamah; Sheba, and Dedan.
verses.verse_html: 9And the sons of Cush; Seba, and Havilah, and Sabta, and Raamah, and Sabtecha. And the sons of Raamah; Sheba, and Dedan.

verses.text_plain: And Cush begat Nimrod: he began to be mighty upon the earth.
verses.verse_html: 10And Cush begat Nimrod: he began to be mighty upon the earth.

verses.text_plain: And Mizraim begat Ludim, and Anamim, and Lehabim, and Naphtuhim,
verses.verse_html: 11And Mizraim begat Ludim, and Anamim, and Lehabim, and Naphtuhim,

verses.text_plain: And Pathrusim, and Casluhim, (of whom came the Philistines,) and Caphthorim.
verses.verse_html: 12And Pathrusim, and Casluhim, (of whom came the Philistines,) and Caphthorim.

verses.text_plain: And Canaan begat Zidon his firstborn, and Heth,
verses.verse_html: 13And Canaan begat Zidon his firstborn, and Heth,

verses.text_plain: The Jebusite also, and the Amorite, and the Girgashite,
verses.verse_html: 14The Jebusite also, and the Amorite, and the Girgashite,

verses.text_plain: And the Hivite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite,
verses.verse_html: 15And the Hivite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite,

verses.text_plain: And the Arvadite, and the Zemarite, and the Hamathite.
verses.verse_html: 16And the Arvadite, and the Zemarite, and the Hamathite.

verses.text_plain: The sons of Shem; Elam, and Asshur, and Arphaxad, and Lud, and Aram, and Uz, and Hul, and Gether, and Meshech.
verses.verse_html:
17The sons of Shem; Elam, and Asshur, and Arphaxad, and Lud, and Aram, and Uz, and Hul, and Gether, and Meshech. ▼
▼ Meshech: or, Mash

verses.text_plain: And Arphaxad begat Shelah, and Shelah begat Eber.
verses.verse_html: 18And Arphaxad begat Shelah, and Shelah begat Eber.

verses.text_plain: And unto Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg; because in his days the earth was divided: and his brother’s name was Joktan.
verses.verse_html:
19And unto Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg; because in his days the earth was divided: and his brother’s name was Joktan. ▼
▼ Peleg: that is, division

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Peleg: that is, division

verses.text_plain: And Joktan begat Almodad, and Sheleph, and Hazarmaveth, and Jerah,
verses.verse_html: 20And Joktan begat Almodad, and Sheleph, and Hazarmaveth, and Jerah,

verses.text_plain: Hadoram also, and Uzal, and Diklah,
verses.verse_html: 21Hadoram also, and Uzal, and Diklah,

verses.text_plain: And Ebal, and Abimael, and Sheba,
verses.verse_html: 22And Ebal, and Abimael, and Sheba,

verses.text_plain: And Ophir, and Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.
verses.verse_html: 23And Ophir, and Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.

verses.text_plain: Shem, Arphaxad, Shelah,
verses.verse_html: 24Shem, Arphaxad, Shelah,

verses.text_plain: Eber, Peleg, Reu,
verses.verse_html: 25Eber, Peleg, Reu,

verses.text_plain: Serug, Nahor, Terah,
verses.verse_html: 26Serug, Nahor, Terah,

verses.text_plain: Abram; the same is Abraham.
verses.verse_html: 27Abram; the same is Abraham.

verses.text_plain: The sons of Abraham; Isaac, and Ishmael.
verses.verse_html: 28The sons of Abraham; Isaac, and Ishmael.

verses.text_plain: These are their generations: The firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth; then Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,
verses.verse_html: 29These are their generations: The firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth; then Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,

verses.text_plain: Mishma, and Dumah, Massa, Hadad, and Tema,
verses.verse_html:
30Mishma, and Dumah, Massa, Hadad, and Tema, ▼
▼ Hadad: also called, Hadar

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Hadad: also called, Hadar

verses.text_plain: Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael.
verses.verse_html: 31Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael.

verses.text_plain: Now the sons of Keturah, Abraham’s concubine: she bare Zimran, and Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah. And the sons of Jokshan; Sheba, and Dedan.
verses.verse_html: 32Now the sons of Keturah, Abraham’s concubine: she bare Zimran, and Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah. And the sons of Jokshan; Sheba, and Dedan.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Henoch, and Abida, and Eldaah. All these are the sons of Keturah.
verses.verse_html: 33And the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Henoch, and Abida, and Eldaah. All these are the sons of Keturah.

verses.text_plain: And Abraham begat Isaac. The sons of Isaac; Esau and Israel.
verses.verse_html: 34And Abraham begat Isaac. The sons of Isaac; Esau and Israel.

verses.text_plain: The sons of Esau; Eliphaz, Reuel, and Jeush, and Jaalam, and Korah.
verses.verse_html: 35The sons of Esau; Eliphaz, Reuel, and Jeush, and Jaalam, and Korah.

verses.text_plain: The sons of Eliphaz; Teman, and Omar, Zephi, and Gatam, Kenaz, and Timna, and Amalek.
verses.verse_html:
36The sons of Eliphaz; Teman, and Omar, Zephi, and Gatam, Kenaz, and Timna, and Amalek. ▼
▼ Zephi: or, Zepho

verses.text_plain: The sons of Reuel; Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.
verses.verse_html: 37The sons of Reuel; Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Seir; Lotan, and Shobal, and Zibeon, and Anah, and Dishon, and Ezer, and Dishan.
verses.verse_html: 38And the sons of Seir; Lotan, and Shobal, and Zibeon, and Anah, and Dishon, and Ezer, and Dishan.

verses.text_plain: And the sons of Lotan; Hori, and Homam: and Timna was Lotan’s sister.
verses.verse_html:
39And the sons of Lotan; Hori, and Homam: and Timna was Lotan’s sister. ▼
▼ Homam: or, Hemam

verses.text_plain: The sons of Shobal; Alian, and Manahath, and Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. And the sons of Zibeon; Aiah, and Anah.
verses.verse_html:
40The sons of Shobal; Alian, and Manahath, and Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. And the sons of Zibeon; Aiah, and Anah. ▼
▼ Alian: also called, Alvan
 , ▼
▼ Shephi: also called, Shepho

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Alian: also called, Alvan
▼ Shephi: also called, Shepho

verses.text_plain: The sons of Anah; Dishon. And the sons of Dishon; Amram, and Eshban, and Ithran, and Cheran.
verses.verse_html:
41The sons of Anah; Dishon. And the sons of Dishon; Amram, and Eshban, and Ithran, and Cheran. ▼
▼ Amram: or, Hemdan

verses.text_plain: The sons of Ezer; Bilhan, and Zavan, and Jakan. The sons of Dishan; Uz, and Aran.
verses.verse_html:
42The sons of Ezer; Bilhan, and Zavan, and Jakan. The sons of Dishan; Uz, and Aran. ▼
▼ Jakan: or, Akan

verses.text_plain: Now these are the kings that reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the children of Israel; Bela the son of Beor: and the name of his city was Dinhabah.
verses.verse_html: 43Now these are the kings that reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the children of Israel; Bela the son of Beor: and the name of his city was Dinhabah.

verses.text_plain: And when Bela was dead, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.
verses.verse_html: 44And when Bela was dead, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.

verses.text_plain: And when Jobab was dead, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his stead.
verses.verse_html: 45And when Jobab was dead, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his stead.

verses.text_plain: And when Husham was dead, Hadad the son of Bedad, which smote Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Avith.
verses.verse_html: 46And when Husham was dead, Hadad the son of Bedad, which smote Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Avith.

tokens.text: in his stead: and the name

verses.text_plain: And when Hadad was dead, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead.
verses.verse_html: 47And when Hadad was dead, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead.

verses.text_plain: And when Samlah was dead, Shaul of Rehoboth by the river reigned in his stead.
verses.verse_html: 48And when Samlah was dead, Shaul of Rehoboth by the river reigned in his stead.

verses.text_plain: And when Shaul was dead, Baal–hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his stead.
verses.verse_html: 49And when Shaul was dead, Baal–hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his stead.

verses.text_plain: And when Baal–hanan was dead, Hadad reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Pai; and his wife’s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.
verses.verse_html:
50And when Baal–hanan was dead, Hadad reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Pai; and his wife’s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab. ▼
▼ Hadad: or, Hadar
 , ▼
▼ Pai: or, Pau

tokens.text: in his stead: and the name

verses.text_plain: Hadad died also. And the dukes of Edom were; duke Timnah, duke Aliah, duke Jetheth,
verses.verse_html: 51Hadad died also. And the dukes of Edom were; duke Timnah, duke Aliah, duke Jetheth,

verses.text_plain: Duke Aholibamah, duke Elah, duke Pinon,
verses.verse_html: 52Duke Aholibamah, duke Elah, duke Pinon,

verses.text_plain: Duke Kenaz, duke Teman, duke Mibzar,
verses.verse_html: 53Duke Kenaz, duke Teman, duke Mibzar,

verses.text_plain: Duke Magdiel, duke Iram. These are the dukes of Edom.
verses.verse_html: 54Duke Magdiel, duke Iram. These are the dukes of Edom.
